author: Sarah E. Needleman
title: FanDuel Adds Competitive Videogames to Roster
text:
FanDuel Inc. earlier this month acquired Fandom Gaming Inc., which goes by the name AlphaDraft, in a move to add competitive videogames to the daily fantasy sports site’s roster of leagues.
Terms of the deal weren’t disclosed. The news comes a day after FanDuel’s main rival, DraftKings Inc., began allowing its customers to create virtual teams... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
